caption: The food is good, but don't get ripped off. They've tried it on me 3 times now with gift certificates, claiming the certificate was already used up even if it's brand new. At first i thought it was an honest mistake but it's clearly intentional because it's happened to me 3 of the last 6 or 7 times i was there. If you're ever told your gift certificate has a lower value or was already used, it's a lie. Second scam, their published prices (website, in store menus) aren't real so be prepared for a surprise number when you pay. Each item is a couple dollars over whatever you thought it was. Very unprofessional.
Fantastic food, excellent service, highly recommended!!!

The food was excellent! My daughter and i had the shrimp dumplings, chicken egg rolls and potstickers appetizer then the spicy crunchy tuna, spicy tuna, and salmon rolls (pictured below). I also had the mango martini. The waitress is a sweetheart. We will be back 😊

The staff here is really nice so I give them points for that.  However, the chicken on our entrees to go were extremely bland. There was no speck of salt or seasoning added at all.  Also, we got CANNED mushrooms, tomato, and pinneapples which added a terrible flavor to the already unsavory sauce. This is just unacceptable for a restaurant meal.  Really dissappointed in the quality.
I ordered the pad thai and it was extremely bland. Save yourself the trip and go to noodles and company instead.

My reviews have been read over 2000 times so obviously - I know what I'm talking about.  Pay too much and get tofu with extra vegetables. Do not just get tofu. There will be no vegetables.  The rice portion is calorie appropriate which is to say, there isn't enough rice.  The taste is worth the money. They move fast. Spice level is real. It's humorous the order they list it on the app.  I only eat vegetarian sushi. Because I'm a Philistein I can't even get auto correct to spell that word correctly.  Please read my reviews. I like the nice notes Google sends me.
This is my family’s favorite Thai food and sushi restaurant. The food is delicious and reasonably priced. Delivery is prompt. Plus, it is a family run business so they really care.
Good, varied menu, super friendly service and a pleasure to be able to dine in again!
Friendly and tasty spot! Best Thai for the Old Town and Gold Coast area, their curries are our go-to with a side of veggie egg rolls. Great prices and always a few discounts to use.
The service and food was amazing. Will go again.
Recently tried Tiparos for the first time, and their take out was AMAZING!!!
Food is always great and consistent! My favorite restaurant in the area. Very friendly staff and great service.

Tiparos is the best sushi place in Old Town. Hands down. If you are looking for a great BYOB in the area, this is your place. Apps, and sushi is amazing. Friendly staff and great atmosphere. Can’t wait to recommend to others!!!!
Food was good. Friend thought the pad thai was a bit bland, but it tasted a bit better day 2. Overall a good place and I'd be willing to try it again.
Thai food and the setting here is above par. it's so appetizing. there was quick, helpful, and friendly service. this place has a cool design. they have so many reviews for a reason.
thai food, so great. I give this place double thumbs up.

Hands down one of the best restaurants in Chicago. I love Thai food and I've been a coming here for at least 15 or more years.  My favorite is definitely pad Thai with extra vegetables wet glass of a plum wine on the side.  Wink wink.  Their food is always fresh abd  Delicious. Highly recommend this place
Nice place for quality Thai food. The staff was very friendly and attentive. Prices were fair. Reminds me of a place in New York I loved to visit.
Decent sushi and pad Thai.
Delicious
Staff has been super nice and the food has been great.
If you're looking for consistently good service, large portions, and fair prices, Tiparos is your spot. I've always been impressed by their food and have been going here for nearly 13 years.
Delicious Thai food at great prices.
A lot of food and very tasty!

Excellent Thai food. They also have sushi which is very good too. Wish they were out in the suburbs because I live in the suburbs. And I only go here when I visit my dad. Good pricing. Can go here on budget. I go here whenever I can go downtown. The only downside is they don’t serve Sushi until 4:00pm and they should really start serving sushi when the restaurant opens.

Very good restaurant needs a location in the northwest suburbs as it is too far for us for really good food and service only downside is they don’t serve sushi until 4:00pm This is the best Thai food I have ever had.
Stale chicken in all the dishes. We ordered red curry, cashew chicken and chicken satay for sunday lunch. Avoid.
Really good beef pad see eiw, spicy tuna roll and salmon avocado roll. Pad thai was a bit too sweet.

I celebrated my graduation last night in this fine place. happy to tell that it was a outstanding evening and the place was indeed one of the reasons for the successful meeting. The stuff  cooperated in a very nice way, the cooking was tasty and my guests were very  thrilled. We shall absolutely come back again for more joyful events. thanks very much.

I love this restaurant! They have great dishes, their menu is varied, The chef in that place is an expert, I love a lot trying all their dishes. The food is consistently good, the attitude towards the clients  is helpful. I  go often to this restaurant and I not even once was discontended. I recommend this place.
They serve big portions and for affordable prices. kind staff members. Highly recommended.
Yummy, not so expensive dining.
Great taste of Thai contemporary food!
The service is regularly efficient, great vibes, friendly employees. Will return here again when I get in the area.
Cute place for a low key meal. And it's BYOB!
(Translated by Google) Excellent Thai food! Good atmosphere, prices commensurate. Highly recommended!  (Original) Excelente.comida Thai! Buen ambiente, precios acordes. Muy recomendable!

This restaurant is very welcoming and affordable.  I ordered the Sushi Rice and Brown Rice using the Ritual App and both orders were very tasty.  This is my first time visiting a Thai restaurant and won’t be the last.  Thank you Tiparos
This place is worth visiting. They serve big portions for affordable prices. Consistently well kept and with excellent mood. Will come visit again.
Good Lunchs in Chicago
I had a superb experience in this spot. We enjoyed the nice environment and the menu. The waiters were super amiable. I’m happy we eventually decided to eat here.
Don't go for sushi... Not great.

They often close early and fail to keep consistent hours.  Post hours and follow them please.  Also there food is not so great.  Their Thai Tea comes out as a slushie without warning (should say frozen thai tea on the menu) and their Pad Thai seems like it's made with spaghetti noodles.

Very very bad. I used to eat here almost 10 years ago. I was so excited to enjoy  lunch here. We walked in and the waitress was eating lunch in the open. When our food arrived it was cold and all 3 dishes had hair in them. Very disappointed

My wife's Mussaman curry was very good. I had chicken teriyaki, carrots and broccoli freshly cooked, just right, and generous amount of chicken. But my chicken was overcooked and tough. Sodas are served by the can, so no refills.

Read the FINE LINE / DISH DESCRIPTION!  Some dishes come with Shrimp for Menu Price, SOME have basic protein add-in price.  LUNCH SPECIAL is priced less with less portion. NOT a savings. Plus, BEEF is extra. What ever happened to Chicken or Beef, & extra fee for shrimp?  SKIP the Veggie Potsticker as there is nothing in it! Photo attached.  PAD KHEE MAO is alright. You know, I always have issues with sloppy, lazy, rough chopping. Spicy.  Better Value -- (1) Lunch Special SPICY BASIL FRIED RICE is an entire soup bowl portion with a brown bag, (2) Lunch Special CRAB RANGOON was bursting cream cheese from it's dough seams.  SERVICE is slow & distracted as it's only 1 person that is also handling the phone.
Crab rangoons are special.

Ordered spicy basil chicken with peanut sauce to go, pretty underwhelmed with my meal. I specifically asked for the chicken to be medium spicy yet the entire dish was bland and under seasoned. Though I found the inclusion of mushrooms to be unique, there were far too many relative to the other vegetables in the dish. Likely will not return.
One of the best Thai restaurants I've ever been to the servers are friendly, the food is amazing, and they don't rush you like other restaurants.
Amazing food. Hands down the best Thai I have ever had. Servers were very friendly and the background music was current and upbeat!
Food is fresh and always delicious
Pretty expensive but good food
Great food at a good price
Decent Thai food. Never too busy.
Not bad prices and pretty good selection but food left lots to be desired
Descent place to eat near Lincoln Park. There is a variety of options to choose from besides Sushi. Great place to go for the picky eaters and the adventurous.
Awesome Thai food! The Rama was amazing.
My favorite place for tasty thai food. It has a good interior.
thai food, very satisfying. i often meet people here to talk. similar to a place in denver i loved.
The food is excellent!
A family tradition

Impressed. We were a little skeptical from outside. But half a dozen meals (some dine-in, some to-go) we're sold.  Kiddo loves a side of noodles in miso soup. Dad is all about the green curry or pad Kee maow, mom is all about the Philly roll and chicken fried rice.  Oh and all the waitresses absolutely adore children
Nice little spot. Been coming here for years. Great food at decent prices!
Good dine-in service, good food, good price, large selection. Rice stick noodles were great.

The service and sushi was good, but the salmon teriyaki was kindof bland. Also, the cocktail I had was kinda weak. I wouldn't go out of my way for this place but if I'm close I'd definitely go back for the sushi.

Wow, just wow. My first job as a kid was at an Asian restuarant that I have never seen its equal in quality of food.  With the first bite of food, I was brought back to that restaurant from 25 years ago.  Great portions, great price, the best food!  Looking forward to coming back.
Great meal for an awesome price!! Try the masuman!!!!

Very cozy ambiance, yummy chicken satay and sushi (very wide variety if different rolls to try!), the Thai iced coffee was delicious! The lighting was really nicely dimmed and glowy which really added to the low key ambiance. Can't wait to come back!
This is the best Tom Ka Gai soup I've had in years. It is delicious.

Fast, clean, nice place. Pad Thai tastes different than other places. Good portions for the price and they have lunch specials, Yay!! My not so pleasant experiences here had to do with stuck up older neighborhood customers who think they need to be taken care of before anyone else and interrupt your order without excusing themselves. Thank god for the well educated staff and the nice service they provide at this place. Enjoy :)
Always stop here!

Service was poor, i had to go get my chili I asked for twice , myself.  Never asked if food was okay. The fried soft shell crab was very greasy and had no flavor. Servers avoided the table the whole time, until time for the bill, when they were over-the- top smiling for a tip..

The Pad Thai has a very strange sweet flavor. The vegetable pot stickers I enjoyed, but my pot sticker expert of a wife did not enjoy them. The miso soup was good - but I’ve yet to have bad miso soup.
Great restaurant!! The food is real authentic Thai food!! The service was very nice!!
Great food, very friendly staff.

A nice restaurant with relaxing atmosphere!  Food is great but in one occasion, it seemed, they had a different cook that didn't know how to cook be the food was not good.  Have been back and food was great again.
Wonderful staff and delicious.
Always good and consistent!
Such a fun place and the owner (guy behind the counter in my pic) was so friendly and humorous. Food came quickly and the waiter was great as well! The sushi was super scrumptious! I loved it here
Delicious food! Fast service! 10/10 would recommend!
Awesome food with wide range of options to choose from.

Very simple place - nothing fancy, but despite that their sushi rolls are surprisingly good and fresh. Be aware that the prices online and on the actual menu is different. Their miso soup are twice as much as it is shown online. Owner said that he will update the menu with the Google. Anyway, this place is worth visiting for a quick lunch stop
Serenity

I had a great time eating at Tiparos,  there is not a single dish that I did not enjoy. The servers were very nice and the service was fast. I would highly recommend the Tom kha, pad se you, and chicken satay.
Just pick anything off their menu and it’s delicious. Their soups... awesome! They serve beer and martinis!
Love the teriyaki chicken .
Good thai for a reasonable price. Always quick, too.
Fantastic fresh food and nice owners!  Rama chicken is just one of a dozen delicious dishes at Tiparos.
Goid food, and Good service.  Prices reasonable and large portions.
Service is very friendly.. the food is delicious and the sushi #1 in the city.
Over twenty minutes and we never received our drink order. We ended up having to walk out to make our appointment.
Great food and service!
(Translated by Google) I'm Alexandra here you eat delicious  (Original) Soy Alexandra aquí se come rico
Moved right across the street So good

Servers were extremely rude and inattentive. Place wasn't even busy yet the servers weren't around. Our server forgot part of our order and wasnt apologetic. Charged us for extra things we didnt order. Food was average at best. Awful experience.
Not as authentic...husband food came out cold..miso soup is extra.  Waitress wasn't too friendly.  Just not good service.
This place is a gem. The food is fantastic. We ordered two entrees to split. Rama Chicken and Pepper & Garlic Chicken. Both were delicious. I highly recommend this restaurant.

(Translated by Google) Service not particularly warm, satisfactory decoration, correct prices. The dishes chosen were not bad but rather bland: plate of assortments Tiparos, grilled duck, brown rice, chicken noodle soup and maki. Pity...  (Original) Service pas particulièrement chaleureux, décoration satisfaisante, prix corrects. Les plats choisis n'étaient pas mauvais mais plutôt fades: assiette d'assortiments Tiparos, canard grillé, riz brun, chicken noodle soup et makis. Dommage...

If I had eaten in the restaurant rather than taken out I would have refused to pay. This was a huge disappointment. Food was beyond bland and the noodles where overcooked. There wasn't  enough sauce on the noodles, you couldn't even distinguish the flavor. The tofu wasn't seasoned at all. I was starving having not eaten lunch that day and didn't even finish half of my order. Worst meal I have payed for in Chicago.

The food was great and inexpensive, parking was easy, and staff was really friendly.  The owner offered to make sushi for us even though the sushi bar is closed until 4 on the weekends.  Will definitely come back next time I'm going to the beach.
Very friendly waiter and food was great. Some dishes are very spicey.
This place was excellent! Just get the Pad Thai and you won't be disappointed. I sub chicken for tofu.
Just okay.
This is one of my favorite places to get food in Chicago.
Keeps giving you the wrong food terrible service and rude waiters.never go here
Enjoyed their food. It didn't blow me away, but I thought it was pretty good for the price. The staff has been helpful on the occasions that I've been.
Loved the starters
Really good and affordable thai/sushi food. I love coming here for the curry and getting one sushi roll. The service is great and the food is always consistently good. Highly recommend!
I've been going here since 1999. This place has affordable food. I highly recommend the basil chicken fried rice. You must try the Thai Tea. Excellent service and friendly staff.

I miss this place so much!  I would go with a very dear friend of mine.  She introduced me to this fine Thai Restaurant and I feel in love with everything about it.  I will always cherish those memories with my friend, the great guest and the staff.  I miss the fresh spring rolls that I can't find any where else.  Oh!  And their crab rangoons are the best ever!      Tiparos I promise on my next visit to my home town, I'll stop by for a wonderful appetizer.  An awesome entree and the best desert.
Ok for the price but it was a bit dirty when I went
Love their food.
Prices were good but food was not authentic Thai. Just "okay".
One of the best Thai restaurants in Chicag.  So authentic.  Excellent sushi options too!!
Cooker are Mexican they don't know how to cook Thai food. This is a kind of food not Thai food . Really disappointed.if u wanted Thai taste this place is not for u.
I would not go back, 2 star Thai food, accompanied by 1 star service.
I have never had Veg Pad Thai like this anywhere else!
Great BYOB before going out in the area
The chicken pad thai is delicious!

Thai food! It's pretty good - the tom yum soup was a tease (in a good way) - I had one little bowl but it was flavored very well. It left me wanting more. Angel wings were also pretty good. The green curry with chicken and the beef Pad see we were also a delight. Nice place for Thai food!

Delivery order, soup and ice tea spilled in bags; the little broth that was left in the container turned out to be not vegetarian as I had ordered it; pad Thai dishes (both chicken and tofu) bland taste, I asked they make the tofu option with no peanuts, well they forgot about that too; only one spicy sauce; the fried rice tastes good, and it would be even better if it wasn't dry as if it's 2 days old. You know that dry taste when you warm it up from the fridge the second day? However, the crab rangoon is excellent, and they did offer to bring me another container of broth and another ice tea. Too bad I spent $57; not worth it! Try another place!
You go for the thai and keep coming back for the sushi. Fresh and delicious. You can't go wrong with either.  Outside seating available and fast delivery. Neighborhood favorite.
Great food at a great price. Definitely my favorite Thai/sushi place in the city.
ordered chicken satay and pad kee mao...the chicken satay is tough :(  pad kee mao was okay...not tons of flavor...
Consistent and great tasting Thai food. The owner Paul is friendly (he helped me find my phone after I dropped it in the snow and did not realize it for an hour, he dug through the snow with me).

After moving to Old Town I thought I'd try this out!  Now it has become my go-to take out place although I have dined in once and enjoyed that as well.  The staff is friendly and the food is delicious.

I first walked in to find a packed, but quiet restaurant filled with authentic Thai decor.  I was instantly welcomed by the stewardess, and walked to the Sushi bar.  I have to say, it smelled great.  I indulged into a California Roll and some Potstickers: They were the best I've ever tasted.  After I finished my Bubble Tea, I strolled out and walked home.  To sum it up, it was worth it.
Dont wast your money here not authentic thai food the owners were so rude , we need to pay for the mistake cooked dish and the owner yell to us bad services
This is hidden secret in the gold coast. They have extremely affordable and delicious Thai food and sushi. The staff is friendly, and the food comes very quickly.

Love Tiparo's crab rangoon appetizer and great pad see eiw with beef and pad thai with chicken noodle dishes. Tiparos also has sushi options available as well as Chinese dishes, salads and a range of entrees - love the Rama chicken with peanut sauce and broccoli.
I've only had Tiparos Thai Restaurant delivered, so I truly can't comment on the decor or service. Great thai food and the crab rangoon is delicious.

Was excited to find a place that delivered sushi but the delivery guy just handed me the bag with one hand (cell phone on the other ear) and jetted quickly (kind of a reverse snatch?) Anyway, good thing about it is he gave me no time to tip him. It was VERY RUDE. I had to calm down before I could enjoy my sushi which was very good. (I've never been in this place so I put Excellent for the Decor)
Tasty crab rangoons. Really good pad thai & reasonable prices. Walking distance from home & also convenient delivery on cold nights.
Crab rangoon. Get it. The pad thai and curry fried rice are always the best.

It was really nice and very quiet. I ate there about 2 times already but the food is good. I enjoyed their Cashew Chicken and their Pepper steak. The spices are perfect, adn you can order them any way you like to your preference.
consistently good food.  great delivery.

Really tasty! Masamun curry sticks to your ribs without being too heavy, pad see eiw is great, too. If you're hankering for pork, they do a slightly tangy bbq pork that's cut in thin, slightly dry slices. That, the tofu and chicken are really good in all dishes I've had.
